The '''Monduth''' were a sentient race. They were sensitive to the Bogan, or [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|dark side]]. They had mutiple eyes, stood larger than most [[Human/Legends|Humans]], and were physically formidable, able to throw an adult male Human across a room.

[[Luke Skywalker/Legends|Luke Skywalker]] had a run-in with a Monduth at the [[Chalmun's Spaceport Cantina/Legends|Mos Eisley Cantina]]. The Monduth, along with a Human and a small, rodent-like alien, tried to pick a fight with him. [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] made an effort to intervene, though the fight ended abruptly when Starkiller killed two of the thugs with his [[Lightsaber/Legends|laser sword]].

==Behind the scenes==
*This creature eventually developed into [[Ponda Baba/Legends|Ponda Baba]], an [[Aqualish/Legends|Aqualish]] in [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''Star Wars'': Episode IV ''A New Hope'']].

*Interestingly, when the Aqualish reappeared in the [[Prequel trilogy]], they were depicted with an additional set of eyes, making them resemble the Monduths more strongly.

